#+TITLE: Poly Org Demo
#+AUTHOR: Shapeshifter
#+OPTIONS: toc:nil

Welcome to the world of poly-org! Below are a few source blocks using different languages.
When opened with `poly-org-mode`, each block will be edited using its own major mode!

* Python Block

#+BEGIN_SRC python
def greet(name):
    print(f"Hello, {name}! Welcome to the Multiverse.")

greet("Shapeshifter")
#+END_SRC

* Emacs Lisp Block

#+BEGIN_SRC emacs-lisp
(defun polymode-power ()
  "Return a message celebrating polymode!"
  (message "Polymode activated in Org Mode!"))

(polymode-power)
#+END_SRC

* Shell Script Block

#+BEGIN_SRC sh
#!/bin/bash
echo "Running in shell mode with Poly-Org!"
date
#+END_SRC

* LaTeX Block

#+BEGIN_SRC latex
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}
Hello from within a LaTeX block!
\end{document}
#+END_SRC

* JavaScript Block

#+BEGIN_SRC js
function echo(message) {
    console.log("Poly-Org says: " + message);
}

echo("This is JavaScript inside Org!");
#+END_SRC

* End

Thatâ€™s it! Tweak the blocks, run the code, and try switching major modes. Poly-org will adapt!